{"time": "20:43:54.172", "event": "llm_output", "round": 0, "content": "### What’s happening with the current plot  \n\nThe code we ran creates the cumulative series like this:\n\n```r\nCum_Strategy = cumprod(1 + Strategy_Return) - 1\nCum_BuyHold  = cumprod(1 + Daily_Return)    - 1\n```\n\n`cumprod(1 + r)` builds a **price‑level multiplier** (1 → 1.02 → 1.05 …).  \nIf you plot the raw `cumprod(1 + r)` you’ll see the y‑axis start at **1**, because the first value of the multiplier is 1 (the “starting price”).  \n\nWhen we subtract 1 (as in the code above) the series now represen", "empty": false}
