{"time": "20:43:08.811", "event": "llm_output", "round": 3, "content": "**Step 4 – Lag the trend‑following signal by one day**  \nWe create a new column `Signal_lag` that contains yesterday’s signal (`Signal`). This ensures that today’s position is based on information that would have been available at the market open, giving the strategy realistic (live‑environment) predictive power.\n\n```r\n# Lag the signal so today's position uses yesterday's information\nbitcoin_daily_5y <- bitcoin_daily_5y %>%\n  mutate(Signal_lag = lag(Signal, n = 1))\n```", "empty": false}
