{"time": "12:35:16.562", "event": "llm_output", "round": 1, "content": "### Step 2 – Build the trend‑following signal without look‑ahead bias  \nWe create `Signal` = 1 when yesterday’s closing price was above yesterday’s 30‑day moving average, otherwise 0. Missing values (the first row) are set to 0.\n\n```r\nbitcoin_daily_5y <- bitcoin_daily_5y %>%\n  mutate(Signal = ifelse(lag(Close) > lag(MA30), 1, 0)) %>%\n  tidyr::replace_na(list(Signal = 0))\n```", "empty": false}
